This is a textbook case of **coverage-gaming** — every production method is invoked, but almost nothing is actually verified. Here's the severity-ranked audit:

---

## 🔴 CRITICAL — Assert-Free Tests (coverage with zero verification)

These tests execute code paths but prove nothing. A bug in any of them would never be caught.

**1. `AddProduct_Works` (line 17)** — No assert at all. Doesn't verify the product was persisted.
```csharp
// Fix:
_catalog.AddProduct(product);
var saved = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNotNull(saved);
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", saved.Name);
Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, saved.Price);
```

**2. `UpdatePrice_Works` (line 32)** — Calls `UpdatePrice` but never checks the price changed.
```csharp
// Fix:
_catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated!.Price);
```

**3. `RemoveProduct_Works` (line 38)** — Calls `RemoveProduct` but never checks the product is gone.
```csharp
// Fix:
_catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNull(_catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001"));
```

**4. `GetProductCount_Works` (line 63)** — No data seeded, no assert. Would pass even if `GetProductCount` returned -1.
```csharp
// Fix:
Assert.AreEqual(0, _catalog.GetProductCount());
_catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
Assert.AreEqual(1, _catalog.GetProductCount());
```

**5. `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (line 68)** — Applies a 10% discount but never verifies any price changed. A discount calculation bug (e.g. `Price * fraction` instead of `Price * (1 - fraction)`) would sail through.
```csharp
// Fix:
_catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);
Assert.AreEqual(8.991m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001")!.Price);
Assert.AreEqual(17.991m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-002")!.Price);
```

**6. `ImportFromCsv_Works` (line 85)** — Imports a CSV row but never checks a product was actually created.
```csharp
// Fix:
_catalog.ImportFromCsv("SKU-001,Widget,9.99");
var imported = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNotNull(imported);
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", imported.Name);
Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, imported.Price);
```

